subSubSection.paragraph:
COLORATION (
Fig. 1B
). — Antennular and antennal peduncles orangish-red; ocular peduncles orangish-red, cornea pale orange (black on preserved specimens). Chelipeds (
Fig. 3B
) and ambulatory legs (
Fig. 4B
) with composite coloured rings, made of one white bluish median band, flanked by two bright red rings; these composite rings are set against an orange background. Chelipeds with composite rings disposed on meri, carpi, and palms of chelae; fingers of chelae almost uniformly pale orange, without composite coloured rings. Ambulatory legs with composite coloured rings on meri, carpi and propodi; dactyls pale orange without composite coloured rings; terminal claws black. Shield white; live coloration of the abdomen unknown, abdomen uniformly white after three weeks in preservative.
